sql:
SELECT d.distance
FROM Student s1
JOIN Student s2 ON 1=1
JOIN Direct_distance d ON 
    (d.city1_code = s1.city_code AND d.city2_code = s2.city_code)
    OR (d.city1_code = s2.city_code AND d.city2_code = s1.city_code)
WHERE s1.Fname = 'Linda' AND s1.LName = 'Smith'
  AND s2.Fname = 'Tracy' AND s2.LName = 'Kim';
question: How far do Linda (first name) Smith (last name) and Tracy (first name) Kim (last name) live?

sql:
SELECT dd.distance
FROM Direct_distance dd
JOIN Student s1 ON (dd.city1_code = s1.city_code OR dd.city2_code = s1.city_code)
JOIN Student s2 ON (dd.city1_code = s2.city_code OR dd.city2_code = s2.city_code)
WHERE s1.Fname = 'Linda' AND s1.LName = 'Smith'
  AND s2.Fname = 'Tracy' AND s2.LName = 'Kim'
  AND s1.city_code <> s2.city_code
  AND ((dd.city1_code = s1.city_code AND dd.city2_code = s2.city_code)
       OR (dd.city1_code = s2.city_code AND dd.city2_code = s1.city_code));
question: How far do Linda (first name) Smith (last name) and Tracy (first name) Kim (last name) live?

sql:
SELECT 
  c1.city_name AS Linda_City, 
  c2.city_name AS Tracy_City, 
  dd.distance 
FROM 
  Student s1
JOIN 
  City c1 ON s1.city_code = c1.city_code
JOIN 
  Student s2 ON s2.Fname = 'Tracy' AND s2.LName = 'Kim'
JOIN 
  City c2 ON s2.city_code = c2.city_code
JOIN 
  Direct_distance dd ON 
    (dd.city1_code = s1.city_code AND dd.city2_code = s2.city_code) OR 
    (dd.city1_code = s2.city_code AND dd.city2_code = s1.city_code)
WHERE 
  s1.Fname = 'Linda' AND s1.LName = 'Smith';
question: How far do Linda (first name) Smith (last name) and Tracy (first name) Kim (last name) live?
